300.subject: MXET
300.courseDescription: Mechatronics I – Mobile Robotic Systems. (2-3). Credit 3. Mechanical, electronic, software, control and communications aspects of embedded intelligence-based electromechanical systems with a focus on mobile robotic platforms. Prerequisites: Grade of C or better in MXET 375, PHYS 207, and ENGR 217 or PHYS 217; grade of C or better in ESET 359 and ESET 369 or concurrent enrollment.

375.subject: MXET
375.courseDescription: Applied Dynamic Systems. (2-3). Credit 3. Study of translational mechanical system dynamics, rotational mechanical system dynamics, electrical system dynamics modeling, electro-mechanical/mechatronics system dynamics, fluid power dynamics and 2 dimensional rigid body dynamics. Prerequisites: Grade of C or better in MMET 275; junior or senior classification in an engineering technology major.

400.subject: MXET
400.courseDescription: Mechatronics II – Industrial Robotic Systems. (2-3). Credit 3. Study and analysis of industrial robotics and automation processes necessary for robot-centric work cell design and operation. Prerequisites: Grade of C or better in MXET 300; grade of C or better in ESET 462 or concurrent enrollment, junior or senior classification in multidisciplinary engineering technology.

635.subject: MXET
635.courseDescription: Advanced Applied Dynamics for Mechatronic Systems. (3-0). Credit 3. Translational mechanical system dynamics, rotational mechanical system dynamics, electrical system dynamics modeling, mechatronics system dynamics, fluid power dynamics, rigid body dynamics and applied dynamics modeling using finite element method; automotive, oil and gas drilling and robotic applications. Prerequisites: Graduate classification or approval of instructor.

681.subject: MXET
681.courseDescription: Seminar. Credit 1. Selected topics presented by the faculty, students and outside speakers. Prerequisites: Graduate classification or approval of instructor.

685.subject: MXET
685.courseDescription: Directed Studies. Credit 1 to 12 each semester. Directed study of topics not within scope of thesis research and not covered by other formal courses. May be repeated for credit. Prerequisites: Graduate classification or approval of instructor.

689.subject: MXET
689.courseDescription: Special Topics in... Credit 1 to 4. Selected topics in an identified area of engineering technology. May be repeated for credit. Prerequisites: Graduate classification or approval of instructor.

691.subject: MXET
691.courseDescription: Research. Credit 1 or more per semester. Research for thesis or dissertation. May be repeated for credit. Prerequisites: Graduate classification or approval of instructor.

692.subject: MXET
692.courseDescription: Professional Study. Credit 1 or more each semester. Approved professional study of project. Prerequisites: Approval of Instructor.
